---
layout: page
post: true
panel_includes:
  - toc
tail_includes:
  - related-posts
  - post-nav
  - comments
---

{% comment %}
The use of post:true above helps the fact that in the Liquid theme,you were able to check the
ORIGINAL layout, not the current one, so this flags to page.liquid that I'm a post.
{% endcomment %}

<div class="post-meta text-muted">
    <span>
		Posted <em>{{ date | date: "%B %e, %Y" }}</em>
		{% assign age = page.date | ageInDays %}
		{% assign twoyears = 365 | times: 2 %}
		{% if age > twoyears %}
		<span class="oldPost">(This post is more than 2 years old.)</span>
		{% endif %}
    </span>


  {% if banner_image %}
    {% capture src %}src="https://static.raymondcamden.com{{ banner_image }}"{% endcapture %}
	{% capture class %}class="preview-img"{% endcapture %}
    {% capture alt %}alt="{{ title | default: "Preview Image" }}"{% endcapture %}

    <div class="mt-3 mb-3">
      <img {{ src }} {{ class }} {{ alt }} width="100%">
    </div>
  {% endif %}

</div> <!-- .post-meta -->

<div class="post-content">
  {{ content }}
</div>

<div class="post-tail-wrapper text-muted">

  <!-- categories -->
  {% if categories.size > 0 %}
  <div class="post-meta mb-3">
    <i class="far fa-folder-open fa-fw mr-1"></i>
    {% for category in categories %}
      <a href='{{ site.baseurl }}/categories/{{ category | slugify | url_encode }}/'>{{ category }}</a>
      {%- unless forloop.last -%}, {%- endunless -%}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  {% endif %}

  <!-- tags -->
  {% if tags.size > 0 %}
  <div class="post-tags">
    <i class="fa fa-tags fa-fw mr-1"></i>
      {% for tag in tags %}
      <a href="{{ site.baseurl }}/tags/{{ tag | slugify | url_encode }}/"
          class="post-tag no-text-decoration" >
        {{- tag -}}
      </a>
      {% endfor %}
  </div>
  {% endif %}

  <div class="post-tail-bottom
    d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mt-3 pt-5 pb-2">

    {% include "post-sharing.liquid" %}

  </div><!-- .post-tail-bottom -->

</div><!-- div.post-tail-wrapper -->
